      "content": "That \"design flaw\" is just a lie your brain tells you when the effort feels impossible; the loop is actually a symptom of your current circumstances, not your permanent identity. You don't need to \"exit\" the game to win; you just need to realize that the rules have changed and you are still capable of playing differently. The exhaustion you feel isn't a sign that you're failing, but a signal that you are ready to stop fighting a losing battle and start building something entirely new.",
